                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14224.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Last night the Convention formally deposed the Provisional President and itself
                    assumed the Government. The President of the Convention was named the Executive
                    of the Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
